{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489329","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489329"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:13:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:13:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"634"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/634"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.29,0.02,0.56,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"634"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78146"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/634"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"634"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63568"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"21"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"489"},{"type":"tags","id":"652"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4965"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"6523"},{"type":"tags","id":"6610"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"12908"},{"type":"tags","id":"12911"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1353"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7481"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42117"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43026"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44259"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78146","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78146"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a two-day history of right calf pain and swelling. She is 37 weeks pregnant with her second child. Her first pregnancy was uncomplicated. She has noticed increasing breathlessness over the past month. She has no significant medical history and takes only pregnancy vitamins.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 85/min, blood pressure 118/75 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. Her right calf is swollen, tender and erythematous compared to the left. Chest examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["CT pulmonary angiogram","Ventilation-perfusion scan","Chest X-ray","Duplex ultrasound of lower limbs","D-dimer"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with signs and symptoms suggestive of deep vein thrombosis (DVT) in pregnancy. The physiological changes of pregnancy increase the risk of venous thromboembolism (VTE) by approximately five-fold.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuplex ultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E of the lower limbs is the most appropriate initial investigation as it is safe in pregnancy, non-invasive, and has good sensitivity and specificity for DVT. If positive, therapeutic anticoagulation can be initiated immediately.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ED-dimer\u003C/strong\u003E testing is not useful in pregnancy as levels are physiologically elevated. There are no validated cut-off values for use in pregnancy, making interpretation unreliable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECT pulmonary angiogram\u003C/strong\u003E involves radiation exposure to both mother and fetus. While the radiation dose is within acceptable limits, it should not be the initial investigation when DVT is the primary concern.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVentilation-perfusion scan\u003C/strong\u003E also involves radiation exposure and would only be considered if pulmonary embolism (PE) is suspected and DVT has been excluded.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChest X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E cannot diagnose PE or DVT and would only be helpful to exclude other causes of breathlessness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf DVT is confirmed on ultrasound, therapeutic low molecular weight heparin should be commenced. Current evidence suggests that further imaging for PE is not necessary unless there are significant cardiorespiratory symptoms, as treatment would be the same.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["D-dimer testing is not useful in pregnancy as concentrations are physiologically elevated","Duplex ultrasound is the first-line investigation for suspected DVT in pregnancy due to its safety and accuracy","If DVT is confirmed, therapeutic anticoagulation should be started without necessarily investigating for PE"],"references":["Robert-Ebadi H, Moumneh T, Le Gal G, Righini M. Diagnosis of Pulmonary Embolism during Pregnancy. Diagnostics (Basel). 2022 Aug 3;12(8):1875. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9406738/","McLintock C, Brighton T, Chunilal S, Dekker G, McDonnell N, McRae S, et al; Councils of the Society of Obstetric Medicine of Australia and New Zealand; Australasian Society of Thrombosis and Haemostasis. Recommendations for the diagnosis and treatment of deep venous thrombosis and pulmonary embolism in pregnancy and the postpartum period. Aust N Z J Obstet Gynaecol. 2012 Feb;52(1):14-22. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21972999/","Thromboprophylaxis and Thromboembolic Disease in Pregnancy, South Australian Perinatal Practice Guideline. In: Department of Health and Aging, Adelaide [online]. 2020; accessed 2020. Available at: https://www.sahealth.sa.gov.au/wps/wcm/connect/a070e7804eedf080b699b76a7ac0d6e4/Thromboprophylaxis+and+Thromboembolic+Disease+in+Pregnancy_PPG_v4_1_14052018.pdf?MOD=AJPERES\u0026amp;CACHEID=ROOTWORKSPACE-a070e7804eedf080b699b76a7ac0d6e4-n5ifkRg\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63568"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"634"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63568","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63568"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-09T14:41:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-09T14:41:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"634"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78146"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/13"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude78","name":"Haematology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"21","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/21"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb5","name":"Vascular Surgery","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synon